A drive-by shooting in Inanda, Durban, claimed the lives of six people on Friday afternoon. The incident happened in Amaoti area. KwaZulu-Natal Police Spokesperson, Brigadier Jay Naicker, said a vehicle with three unknown gunmen inside opened fire to a group of men who were seated behind a tuck shop. Six men, aged between 17 and 26 years old, were killed in the attack, said Naicker. "At this stage information gathered from the scene indicates that the deceased were seated behind the tuck shop, consuming drugs and that the attack might be drug related," he said. "We are appealing to anyone who may have information with regards to the identity of the deceased to contact police at Inanda or Crime stop on 08600 10111."